    "title": "Man arrested for bid to convert family | - Times of India",
    "text": "BAREILLY: A man, who allegedly attempted to change the religion of a Dalit family to Christianity, was booked and arrested by police in the Faridpur area of Bareilly on Thursday evening.A complaint was registered by a resident, Ramgopal Kosi, who stated that Ramesh Chand Massey often visited his village and preached about Christianity to locals. Although Kosi refused to convert, Massey managed to convince his wife, Guddi Devi, and his five children to change their religion. On Thursday, while Kosi was out for work, Massey was performing the rituals to convert his family members to Christianity. Upon learning about it from neighbours, Kosi informed the police. Additional SP (South) Manush Pareek told TOI, \\\"The complainant said that the accused, Ram Chand Massey, allegedly tried to convert a Dalit family to his religion and later misbehaved with the complainant as well. We have booked Massey under sections 504 (criminal intimidation), and 504 (intentional insult) of the IPC along with sections 3 and 5 (1) of the Religious Conversion Act. The case is under investigation, and the accused has been sent to jail.\\\"",
